1.00	Gregg_Olsen	Gregg Olsen	Gregg Olsen (born March 5, 1959, in Seattle, Wash.) is a New York Times and a USA Today bestselling author of eight nonfiction books and six novels, most of which are crime-related. The subjects of his true crime books include convicted child rapist and school teacher Mary Kay Letourneau, product tampering killer Stella Nickell, fasting specialist Linda Burfield Hazzard, and former Amishman and convicted murderer Eli Stutzman.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/GreggolderIII.jpg/225px-GreggolderIII.jpg
